    "review": "Mid movie overall.The teens' plotline was fun and chill to watch.Refreshing attention on Tanvi's \"nice guy/green flag\" boyfriend's \"jokes\" that everyone tries to pass off as harmless but are what really erode a woman's identity and confidence.Beautiful marriage bw JK and Priya (ykwim). Was always pleasant to see their dynamic and interactions as a subversion of trad roles.And the finding yourself trope w the last sharmaji woman was sweet. Reminded me of mom.But overall, just a chill watch. Doesn't feel groundbreaking or preachy or impactful. But still feels good."
